WHILE
===================

Control flow statement.

Syntax:
Do While condition
	[statement block]
Loop

or

Do
	[statement block]
Loop While condition

or

While [condition]
	[statement block]
Wend

Description:
`While` specifies that a loop block will continue if the `condition` following
it evaluates as true. This `condition` is checked during each loop iteration.

Examples:

Dim a As Integer

a = 0
Do While a < 10
    Print "hello"
a = a + 1
Loop

'This will continue to print "hello" on the screen while the condition (a <
10) is met.


Differences from QB:
None

